Inside the Ark, Quickstride looks at Uproar with a not so pleased look on 
his face.

&quot; Ya know, maybe we should never have gone with that idea of yours.&quot;

Uproar gives a sheepish grin.

&quot;Yep, my bad.  As always.&quot;

Quickstride nodds, and sends an oxygen neutralization mist, to clear out the 
stench.

&quot;There, hopefully that&#39;ll work.  And next time, don&#39;t get me in trouble 
again.&quot;

Uproar shrugs.

&quot;Right, ignore my bright ideas, they usually don&#39;t work anyway.&quot;

Quickstride looks to Leo ll and then looks around.

&quot;Hmm, I wonder...  I know there&#39;s a control room around here somewhere.. 
I&#39;m not too good at the technological stuff, but, I used to do a few things, 
like control climate, monitor parameters, that sorta thing.  I wonder if we 
can gain access into the control box, and bypass everything the intruder&#39;s 
done so far?&quot;

Uproar knew where the control box was, he points upwards.

&quot;I know where the box is, but getting to it, that might not be easy.&quot;

On the way back to the Ark, it was clear that Tucson sensed that history was 
partially repeating itself, from the day he had been taken off line during a 
harrowing battle vorns ago.  He was not about to let anyone down a second 
time, and certainly not willing to give up to any of the minions, or 
Hydras&#39;s low life commandoes.

&quot;Talon, I deeply appreciate your concern, and take it greatly into heart. 
But, I&#39;ve failed our factions once before, I can not and will not let that 
happen again.  I have to do this, to stop history from repeating itself.&quot;

Night Shift could tell Tucson was getting ready to put it into battle gear.

&quot;Look, big guy, Talon&#39;s right, you&#39;re in no condition ta put up a fight. 
You&#39;re just gonna get yourself even more damaged than ya already are.&quot;

Rat Trap nodds.

&quot;They&#39;re right Wheels, you can&#39;t just throw yourself out there at sixty 
percent power ratio.  It&#39;s like ya said, sometimes, we don&#39;t always win the 
battle, but eventually we&#39;ll win the war.&quot;

Straight Shot listens too.

&quot;I second that.  No one expects you to always save the day, Tucson.  You&#39;ve 
stretched yourself over your limits far too many times, and it&#39;s time you 
gave yourself time to recharge.&quot;

Tucson sighs.

&quot; There isn&#39;t any time for that Straight Shot.  For every moment I take to 
recharge, more destruction is inflicted.  Lord Elder is in severe disrepair, 
everyone there is in grave danger, and there is an enemy unseen by anyone&#39;s 
scanners that is wreaking havoc in our home.  No, I will not rest until this 
enemy is dealt with.&quot;

Night Shift groans.

&quot;Slag, are you stubborn, Tucson.  You&#39;re not ready for another fight, 
plain&#39;n simple!&quot;

Tucson&#39;s inner cab vibrates, a slight effect of his emotional state.

&quot;Night Shift, don&#39;t.  I&#39;ll do what needs to be done regardless of my 
condition.  I owe you all that much. I owe you your freedom and your saftey. 
I owe everyone that.&quot;

Rat Trap too, gets upset.

&quot; Wheels, will ya just listen ta us this time?!  Ya can&#39;t go inta battle the 
way you are!  There&#39;s more chances of them send&#39;n ya ta the junkyard now 
than there is when you&#39;re runn&#39;n with a hundred percent of your power!  You 
got nothn&#39; left!  You try ta fight now you could go off line permanently! 
YOUR LIFE IS DEPENDING ON IT!&quot;

Straight Shot sits up.

&quot;Thank you Rat Trap, exactly what you said.  If we have to temporarilly take 
you off line Tucson we&#39;ll do that for the sake of saving your aft! Now 
Rodimus doesn&#39;t want you to risk your life, and neither does anyone else! 
For once, LISTEN TO US!&quot;

Tucson pauses.

&quot; Bantor, I - need you to go ahead to back up the other Fuzors, and to see 
if Rodimus needs your help.  I can now drive myself with the energy I&#39;ve got 
left.  I will arrive at the Ark shortly following your arrival there. 
Primus be with you.&quot;

Everyone heaves a sigh of releif. Especially Rat Trap.

&quot;Good choice.  So, what next Wheels?&quot;

Tucson replies as he warms up his engine to continue on his own wheels.

&quot; It seems that whoever has taken control of the Ark, has tampered with it&#39;s 
configuration, via the mainframe.  There is only one thing that could 
possibly interrupt that.  My sonar system.  It has the ability to disrupt 
most alien programming, and perhaps with enough of a disruption, we may - 
just be able to gain control of it again.&quot;

Rat Trap grins.

&quot;Heeeeey, that&#39;s right, that&#39;ll create a weankess in the programming and 
that&#39;s when we can take advantage of reclaiming the configurations.  Better 
get back ta Rodimus and the others about that.&quot;

Tucson acknolwedges and contacts Rodimus.

&quot;Tucson Prime to Rodimus Prime, over.  As soon as I am close enough to the 
ark, I am going to attempt a short range sonar disruption intercept of the 
Ark&#39;s systems.  Hopefully this will cause enough of a falter, for us to 
regain control of the system via an interruption of frequencies.  Tell - 
Legacy to be ready to intercept the mainframe on my mark.  Tucson Prime 
out.&quot;

Straight Shot smiles.

&quot;Now that&#39;s the Tucson Prime I know.  Resourceful yet sensible.  Just like a 
truck should be.&quot;



